Akron Township, Peoria County, Illinois

Akron Township is located in Peoria County, Illinois. As of the 2010 census, its population was 1,068 and it contained 410 housing units. The village of Princeville is partially located in Akron Township along its western border.
Geography.
According to the 2010 census, the township has a total area of , of which (or 99.70%) is land and (or 0.30%) is water.

